  "id": "019d0578-bd76-77b3-aff1-471e04951c0e",
  "content": "# RAG Retrieval Eval Baseline — 2026-03-19\n\nFirst quantitative measurement of corvia's retrieval quality, dogfooding its own knowledge base.\n\n## Results (15 queries, top-10 retrieval)\n- Source Recall@5: 37.5% — less than half of expected sources appear in top 5\n- Keyword Recall: 65% — good keyword coverage\n- MRR: 0.544 — when relevant source found, often at rank 1\n- Overall Relevance: 0.491\n\n## By Category\n- Feature queries: 0.54 relevance (best)\n- Architecture queries: 0.75 (single query, high)\n- Performance queries: 0.33 (worst — latency/benchmark data poorly indexed)\n- API queries: 0.30 (AGENTS.md content not matching well)\n\n## Improvement Opportunities\n1. Performance data (trace latency, benchmark numbers) needs better chunking/indexing\n2. API documentation (MCP tools list) should be chunked to match search patterns\n3. Graph expansion impact needs measurement (currently unmeasured)\n4. Source file matching needs broader patterns (e.g., \"reasoner\" should match reasoner.rs)\n\n## Methodology\n- 15 known-answer queries with expected sources and keywords\n- 5 categories: architecture, feature, config, api, performance\n- 3 difficulty levels: easy, medium, hard\n- Script: benchmarks/rag-retrieval/eval.py",
  "source_version": "mcp",
